<STARTDOC>
macro(style(text))
    (In html, adds tt(text) as an em(inline CSS style) to the next html
tag. E.g, to set a blue color and 30 pixel left-hand side margin for a section
use tt(style(color:blue;margin-left:30px;)sect(Section name)), resulting in
the html markup+nl()
    tt(<h1 style="color:blue;margin-left:30px;">Section name</h1>).nl()
    This macro is only effective with html conversions, and only the last 
tt(style) macro specification of a series is used (e.g.,
tt(style(x)style(y)sect(z)) ignores tt(x), and adds tt(style="y") to
tt(sect(z))). 

 The tt(style) macro is supported by the following macros: tt(bf cell cells
center chapter code dit em figure file itdesc lchapter link lref lsect
lsubsect lsubsubsect nchapter npart nsect nsubsect nsubsubsect paragraph part
quote row sc sect strong subs subsect subsubsect subsubsubsect sups tt url
verb verbinclude).
 )
<>

DEFINEMACRO(style)(1)(\
<html>
    SETSYMBOL(XXstyle)(NOTRANS( style="ARG1"))\
<>
)

